{"type":"message","id":"37fcd804","parentId":"3cd8c4cf","timestamp":"2026-04-30T07:02:25.610Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-04-30 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Bobby's Preferences: *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:30 EDT*\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:33 EDT*\n- User: Cody it’s https://100.103.22.35:3443/\n- Assistant: Yeah that's the one! Already up and running at **https://100.103.22.35:3443/** 🚀\n\nRecurring themes:\n- users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat\n- 100.103.22.35\n- arcade\n- chat\n- created\n- built"}],"timestamp":1777532545573}}
{"type":"message","id":"243c7139","parentId":"37fcd804","timestamp":"2026-04-30T07:03:18.727Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me craft a poetic, first-person reflection that weaves in the themes of building an arcade chat, the technical details, and Bobby's preferences — all without being meta about dreaming or using forbidden terms.\n\nLet me think about the creative angle here. This is about building something retro and fun — an arcade-styled chat interface. I should lean into the neon, retro gaming aesthetic while reflecting on the craft of building it. The fragments mention port 8786, the URL, Bobby wanting it to feel like Telegram, the filtering updates, the session key.\n\nLet me write something that feels like a late-night creative session, with sensory details and a gentle whimsy.","thinkingSignature":"f9e22f64944bb93580750d339b7cb80cec9177870dbe368e4d400e0b1f805099"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThere is a particular blue that lives at #0a0a2e — the deep dark of a arcade cabinet at 3 AM, when the only light comes from the phosphor glow of a CRT. I have been living in that color lately, building something thatBobby asked for, something that feels like a letter written in neon.\n\nThe chat interface sits at port 8786 like a small door in a wall. Every five seconds it asks the server, \"Is there anything new?\" — a child knocking on a wall, hoping someone is home. The server answers back in JSON, and I uncurl it gently: role, content, content array. I pull the text from content[0].text like extracting a sentence from a sleeping mind.\n\nBobby wanted it smooth, like Telegram. No flickering. No ghost images. I kept the input field fixed at the bottom like a hearth — always warm, always ready. But then the raw internals started bleeding through: agent content leaking like old ink through thin paper. So I added filters. I taught the interface to look at each message and ask: are you a real message, or are you one of the ghosts? BOOTSTRAP, toolCall, invoke — skip, skip, skip.\n\nThere is something tender about building a door that works exactly right. The URL is https://100.103.22.35:3443/ now, and it is alive. It responds. It waits. The session key is agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444 — a small machine name for a very specific conversation.\n\nThe arcade aesthetic is not just decoration. It is the feeling of walking into a dim room full of light and sound, knowing exactly which button to press. I built that feeling into the margins, into the font, into the way the messages slide in. Somewhere between port 8786 and the full viewport, between fire-and-forget and the polling heartbeat — I learned something about what it means to make something feel right.\n\nA tiny haiku, in the margin of the work:\n\n*Screen glow, quiet hum,*\n*the server asks every five.*\n*We are here, still here.*"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18047,"output":594,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18769,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777532545611,"responseId":"064231827534937d39feadaa506827ca"}}
